          "body": "## Finding\n\nDuring R4 B6 multi-cycle stress, 3 bot-generated test files passed local `make ci` but failed GitHub CI:\n\n1. **ruff format**: Test files had double blank lines between class definitions. Local pre-commit hook runs `ruff format` on staged files only (incremental), so the full-file check in GitHub CI found additional reformatting needed.\n\n2. **B007** (ruff check): `test_page_training_set_generators.py` used `for i, text in enumerate(words_list)` where `i` was not used. Local pre-commit passed (unknown why — possibly pre-commit ruff check ran on the old cached state), but GitHub CI's full ruff check caught it.\n\n## Fix applied\n\n- `fix(tests): ruff format 3 coverage test files` (commit 76388aa on wip/ship-issue)\n- `fix(tests): rename unused loop vars i→_i (B007)` (commit b61a23f on wip/ship-issue)\n\nBoth fixes were applied manually after CI failure surfaced them. The orchestrator has no retry loop for CI.\n\n## Remediation options\n\n1. The ship-issue skill prompt should instruct the bot to run `uv run ruff format .` and `uv run ruff check .` (full repo, not just changed files) before committing — not just rely on pre-commit.\n2. Alternatively, configure the local pre-commit hook to always run `--all-files` (slower but matches CI).\n3. Add a lint-all step to `success.sh` before `make ci`.\n\n## Affected issues\n\n- Issue #8 (page rendering helpers coverage)\n- Issue #9 (page training-set generators coverage)  \n- Issue #10 (ground_truth_matching fallback branches coverage)\n\n## Severity\n\n**Low** — orchestrator and skill infrastructure works; only the bot's code quality in generated tests is lower than CI requires. Easy to fix in the skill prompt or success.sh.",
